### Overview

This package adds the .NET Desktop Development workload to an existing installation of Visual Studio 2017 (Enterprise, Professional or Community).

The lists of components included in this workload in respective Visual Studio 2017 products are shown here:
- [Enterprise](https://www.visualstudio.com/en-us/productinfo/vs2017-install-product-Enterprise.workloads#net-desktop-development)
- [Professional](https://www.visualstudio.com/en-us/productinfo/vs2017-install-product-Professional.workloads#net-desktop-development)
- [Community](https://www.visualstudio.com/en-us/productinfo/vs2017-install-product-Community.workloads#net-desktop-development)

Visual Studio 2017 must be installed first, for example using Chocolatey packages: [visualstudio2017enterprise](https://chocolatey.org/packages/visualstudio2017enterprise), [visualstudio2017professional](https://chocolatey.org/packages/visualstudio2017professional), [visualstudio2017community](https://chocolatey.org/packages/visualstudio2017community).

### Customizations

The package does not know how to detect installed Visual Studio products yet, so it requires to be told via parameters,
either:

- `--installPath` - the path where the product is installed, for example "C:\Program Files (x86)\Microsoft Visual Studio\2017\Enterprise"

or (both are needed):

- `--productId` - the identifier of the product, for example "Microsoft.VisualStudio.Product.Enterprise"
- `--channelId` - the release channel, should be "VisualStudio.15.Release"

By default, the package installs only components required by the workload. Package parameters can be used to include recommended and/or optional components:

- `--includeRecommended` - Includes the recommended components.
- `--includeOptional` - Includes the optional components.

Example:

    choco install visualstudio2017-workload-manageddesktop --package-parameters "--productId Microsoft.VisualStudio.Product.Enterprise --channelId VisualStudio.15.Release --includeRecommended --includeOptional"
